<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="8b8708ac-f9fa-569f-954d-cb986a7875e9" activityNameId="dcae1eeb-8f60-427c-8d0f-28bb4c841ab3" parentActivityId="44203932-8f7a-5783-aea1-d5359a90fc53" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">white spirit production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">stoddard solvent</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">VM+P Naphtha</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">white spirit</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">sangajol</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">mineral spirit</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of white spirit. The dataset includes the processing of raw materials and chemicals used for production and estimated emissions to air from production (incomplete). It also includes the estimated energy demand and infrastructure of the plant. Solid wastes are omitted.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of pure liquid white spirit. White spirit is a clear colourless solvent with a very low water solubility and a characteristic odour. It is used as an extraction solvent, but also as a cleaning, degreasing and aerosol solvent. It is also used in paints, wood preservatives and laquers, varnishes and asphalt products. According to Stoye (2000), white spirit is predominantly used in the paint industry as a solvent or diluent for oil-based, alkyd resin, chlorinated rubber and some vinyl chloride copolymers paints. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Various types and grades of white spirit are produced from naphtha and kerosene. These petrochemicals are subjected to fractional distillation into appropriate boiling ranges and to different kinds of treatments to obtain the desired type of white spirit. The composition of the solvents may vary due to variation in the composition of the crude oil and also because of differences in refinery processing. In this dataset, white spirit is assumed to be produced by a distillation step, followed by subsequent treatment steps.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Due to missing production data, the inventory is based on theoretical calculations as well as estimations based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Stoye D. (2000) Solvents. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Sixth Edition, June-2001 Electronic Release (ed. Häussinger P., Leitgeb P. and Schmücker B.), 6 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version under: http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/ueic/ull_search_fs.html.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="0bef4135-5b56-4012-a812-b78c9a8218a9">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">1920:Manufacture of refined petroleum products</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data used has no specific geographical origin as it is based on stoechiometric calculations and estimations. It is assumed to be representative of the production processes in this geography. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Production out of naphtha by fractional distillation into appropriate boiling ranges, followed by different kinds of treatments to obtain the desired type of white spirit. The emissions to air are rough estimates.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Date of published literature. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
      <intermediateExchange id="72f8fbaa-794d-5a12-8004-044e4e375dd8" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="RP" amount="1.0" intermediateExchangeId="5f855941-74ab-4d1d-9128-c52f680dc86e" productionVolumeAmount="719000000.0" productionVolumeVariableName="RP_PV" productionVolumeMathematicalRelation="">
        <name xml:lang="en">white spirit</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">White spirit is a clear colourless solvent with a very low water solubility and a characteristic odour. It is used as an extraction solvent, but also as a cleaning, degreasing and aerosol solvent. It is also used in paints, wood preservatives and laquers, varnishes and asphalt products. According to Stoye (2000), white spirit is predominantly used in the paint industry as a solvent or diluent for oil-based, alkyd resin, chlorinated rubber and some vinyl chloride copolymers paints.

Reference(s):
Stoye D. (2000) Solvents. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Sixth Edition, June-2001 Electronic Release (ed. Häussinger P., Leitgeb P. and Schmücker B.), 6 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version under: http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/ueic/ull_search_fs.html.</comment>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.863404133180253" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon allocation</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a301a838-7975-4d89-9e74-8eb77ad03cd1" amount="0.863404133180253" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="c74c3729-e577-4081-b572-a283d2561a75" amount="0.863404133180253" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The most common variety of white spirit is a mixture of saturated aliphatic and alicyclic C7-C12 hydrocarbons with a content of 15-20% (by weight) of aromatic C7-C12 hydrocarbons (ecoinvent v2.2 report 8-part 94). The average composition was assumed as being 82.5% C9.5 saturated aliphatic and alicyclic hydrocarbons (average formula C9.5H20), and 17.5% C9.5 aromatic hydrocarbons (average formula C9.5H9.5).</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6393c14b-db78-445d-a47b-c0cb866a1b25" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="3a0af1d6-04c3-41c6-a3da-92c4f61e0eaa" amount="1.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">dry mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="48c987bb-3144-4872-b5c7-b1389c40be25" amount="45.0" mathematicalRelation="" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e">
          <name xml:lang="en">heating value, net</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Value assumed equal to naphtha.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.5461403278036364" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on inputs: The price of the product has been calculated as a sum of the values of the material and energy inputs for this product. This value is therefore a rough estimation. It may underestimate the real price since there are additional expenses when producing any product. These expences can include for example labour costs, treatment of waste materials and profit for the producer. Please consider carefully whether this level of data quality is acceptable for your application.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a9358458-9724-4f03-b622-106eda248916" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
